    /**
     * A {@link Gtk.ListBoxRow} used to choose from a list of items.
     * 
     * <picture>
     *   <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/combo-row-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *   <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/combo-row.png" alt="combo-row">
     * </picture>
     * 
     * The {@link Adw.ComboRow} widget allows the user to choose from a list of valid
     * choices. The row displays the selected choice. When activated, the row
     * displays a popover which allows the user to make a new choice.
     * 
     * Example of an {@link Adw.ComboRow} UI definition:
     * ```xml
     * <object class="AdwComboRow">
     *   <property name="title" translatable="yes">Combo Row</property>
     *   <property name="model">
     *     <object class="GtkStringList">
     *       <items>
     *         <item translatable="yes">Foo</item>
     *         <item translatable="yes">Bar</item>
     *         <item translatable="yes">Baz</item>
     *       </items>
     *     </object>
     *   </property>
     * </object>
     * ```
     * 
     * The {@link ComboRow.selected} and {@link ComboRow.selected_item}
     * properties can be used to keep track of the selected item and react to their
     * changes.
     * 
     * {@link Adw.ComboRow} mirrors {@link Gtk.DropDown}, see that widget for details.
     * 
     * {@link Adw.ComboRow} is {@link Gtk.ListBoxRow.activatable} if a model is set.
     * 
     * ## CSS nodes
     * 
     * {@link Adw.ComboRow} has a main CSS node with name `row` and the `.combo` style
     * class.
     * 
     * Its popover has the node named `popover` with the `.menu` style class, it
     * contains a {@link Gtk.ScrolledWindow}, which in turn contains a
     * {@link Gtk.ListView}, both are accessible via their regular nodes.
     * 
     * ## Accessibility
     * 
     * {@link Adw.ComboRow} uses the {@link Gtk.AccessibleRole.COMBO-BOX} role.
     * @gir-type Class
     */
