    /**
     * A widget that displays a keyboard shortcut.
     * 
     * <picture>
     *   <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *   <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label.png" alt="shortcut-label">
     * </picture>
     * 
     * The shown shortcut can be set using the {@link ShortcutLabel.accelerator}
     * property.
     * 
     * Optionally, if no shortcut is set, {@link Adw.ShortcutLabel} will display a
     * placeholder set with the {@link ShortcutLabel.disabled_text} property.
     * 
     * The following types of shortcuts can be displayed:
     * 
     * - A single shortcut in {@link Gtk.accelerator_parse} format, e.g. `<Control>C`:
     * 
     *     <picture>
     *       <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-single-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *       <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-single.png" alt="shortcut-label-single">
     *     </picture>
     * 
     * - Multiple alternative shortcuts, separated with spaces, e.g. `<Shift>A Home`:
     * 
     *     <picture>
     *       <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-alternative-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *       <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-alternative.png" alt="shortcut-label-alternative">
     *     </picture>
     * 
     * - A range of shortcuts, separated with `...`, e.g. `<Alt>1...9`:
     * 
     *     <picture>
     *       <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-range-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *       <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-range.png" alt="shortcut-label-range">
     *     </picture>
     * 
     * - Multiple keys pressed at once, separated with `&`, e.g. `Control_L&Control_R`:
     * 
     *     <picture>
     *       <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-multiple-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *       <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-multiple.png" alt="shortcut-label-multiple">
     *     </picture>
     * 
     * - Multiple shortcuts or keys, pressed sequentially, separated with `+`, e.g. `<Control>C+<Control>X`:
     * 
     *     <picture>
     *       <source srcset="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-sequence-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
     *       <img src="https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/libadwaita/doc/1-latest/shortcut-label-sequence.png" alt="shortcut-label-sequence">
     *     </picture>
     * 
     * ::: note
     *     `<`, `>` and `&` need to be escaped as `&lt;`, `&gt;` and `&amp;` when used in UI files.
     * 
     * ## CSS nodes
     * 
     * {@link Adw.ShortcutLabel} has a single CSS node with name `shortcut-label`. The
     * individual keycap labels each have the `.keycap` style class, while the
     * labels separating them have the `.dimmed` style class.
     * 
     * ## Accessibility
     * 
     * {@link Adw.ShortcutLabel} uses the {@link Gtk.AccessibleRole.LABEL} role.
     * 
     * See also: {@link ShortcutsDialog}.
     * @gir-type Class
     * @since 1.8
     */
